```

I'm concerned about this because I'm pretty sure that if a publisher uses <Type>OCD-ID</Type> we won't be able to ingest it because our Java pipeline will reject it as being invalid. Perhaps include a separate check:

if id_type.text.lower() == "ocd-id" and id_type.text.lower() != id_type.text:
  // Error message about improperly-cased ExternalIdentifier Type

Using a generator seems a bit overkill here. Maybe switch to:
```python
@property
def required_display_fields(self):
    return [t[0] for t in self.required_display]
```

Most of py-evm avoids this pattern of creating a list, filling it, then returning it using the `eth_utils.to_tuple` decorator.

```python
def build_powers_with_mutation():
    the_values = []
    for i in range(10):
        the_values.append(2**i)
    return the_values

@to_tuple
def build_powers_no_mutation():
    for i in range(10):
        yield 2**i
```

It is indeed odd but it works :)

```
(env) vishrut@mac azure-cli (monitor-cli) $ az monitor event-categories list
[
